article_title: 25% of ObamaCare's State-Based Exchange Heads Have Resigned Or Taken Medical Leave, More Sure To Follow

article_metadata.author: The Apothecary

og.description: State-based exchanges are looking like the professional sports coaching ranks these days as bad performing ones lose their leaders. More are sure to come as enrollment performance remains poor. The media narrative following the rocky healthcare.gov rollout has been to focus on the “well-performing” state versions. But that is far from reality as a couple of states are carrying the enrollment weight, and a quick review of the early enrollment numbers show how poorly even the best-performing states are really doing.
